# Consultation & Treatment Rework Plan

## Changes Overview

### 1. Replace "Delete Consultation" with "End Consultation"
- **File**: [consultation_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart)
- Remove the delete icon button and [_confirmDelete()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart#235-272) method
- Add "End Consultation" button that:
  - Cancels all future (`upcoming`) sessions in PocketBase
  - Deletes the corresponding synced `appointments` for those cancelled sessions
  - Sets the consultation status to `completed`
  - Shows a confirmation dialog before proceeding

### 2. Consultation Creation: Separate from Treatment Plan
- **File**: [consultation_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart)
- Remove the Treatment Plan Sessions section from the **create** flow (when `consultationId == null`)
- After saving, return the consultation to the caller
- **File**: [patient_profile_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_profile_screen.dart) *(already done)* — already prompts "Create Plan?" after save

### 3. Session #1 Started Today — Bigger Consultation Card
- **File**: [patient_profile_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_profile_screen.dart) → [_buildTreatmentsTab()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_profile_screen.dart#332-467)
- For each consultation card, check if any session linked to it has `session_number == 1` and `status == completed` and `scheduled_date == today`
- If yes, show an expanded card indicating "Session #1 started today"

### 4. Fix Auto-Schedule Engine (CRITICAL)
- **File**: [treatment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/treatment_service.dart) → [createSmartTreatmentPlan()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/treatment_service.dart#154-320)
- **Bug**: The engine checks *only* appointments in the `appointments` collection, but does NOT check the `sessions` table itself. Two treatment plans for different patients can schedule sessions at the exact same time.
- **Fix**: In the slot-checking loop, query BOTH `appointments` AND `sessions` for the given `doctor + date + time`, and ensure the combined count does not exceed `maxBeds`
- Also: after a slot is not found in 8 attempts, fall through to next valid working day instead of defaulting to preferred time

### 5. Rework Consultation Details UI in Patient Profile
- **File**: [consultation_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart) (view mode)
- Add an "Edit Treatment Plan" section that allows:
  - Viewing all sessions with editable dates/times
  - Rescheduling individual sessions (update both session record and synced appointment)
  - A summary of the plan (treatment type, fees, intervals)

## Execution Order
1. Fix auto-schedule engine (most critical bug)
2. Replace delete with end consultation + cancel sessions
3. Separate consultation creation from treatment plan
4. Add session #1 indicator on consultation cards
5. Add treatment plan editing UI
